Business Details - SIC Code 1. Enter the Standard Industrial Code describing the business. This code must be numeric. If the business products cover more than one industry, select a second descriptive code. This is a very large industry standard listing. To browse the complete list, refer to http://www.osha.gov/pls/imis/sic_manual.html.

Business Details - SIC Code 2. Enter the Standard Industrial Code describing the business. This code must be numeric. If the business products cover more than one industry, select a second descriptive code. This is a very large industry standard listing. To browse the complete list, refer to http://www.osha.gov/pls/imis/sic_manual.html.

Business Details - NAICS Code 1. Enter the North American Industry Classification System code that is associated with the business. This code must be numeric. If the business products cover more than one industry, select a second descriptive code. This is a very large industry standard listing. To browse the complete list, refer to http://www.naics.com/referencefiles.htm.

Business Details - NAICS Code 1. Enter the North American Industry Classification System code that is associated with the business. This code must be numeric. To browse the complete list, refer to http://www.naics.com/referencefiles.htm.

Backup Withholding Code - Member backup withholding code. If A-F, member backup withholding applies to all accounts for the member. Any other character indicates that backup withholding does not apply for the member. The backup withholding code at the member level can be set, updated, or deleted. The following are valid codes: • A through F indicate backup withholding applies to all member accounts. • An asterisk (*) removes the code. • Any other alphanumeric code (G through Z, 0 through 9) indicates that backup withholding is not applicable to the member. UMS sets the global withholding for ALL accounts. The account level withholding code in UAT– Update Account Tax Information takes precedence over the member level code. To exclude an account from withholding, use UAT to set an asterisk and clear the withholding code. If the code in UMS is changed, UAT must be performed on each existing account to exclude it from withholding or to assign a different code than set in UMS.
